  "Andrea Della Valle and his brother, Diego, are billionaires thanks to their majority ownership of Italian luxury goods maker Tod's S.p.A.",
  "He is the vice chairman of the global shoe- and purse-maker that his grandfather founded in the early 1900s as a small shoe factory.",
  "The brothers also own stakes in Vespa-maker Piaggio, media conglomerate RCS MediaGroup, investment bank Mediobanca and soccer team ACF Fiorentina.",
  "Andrea was Fiorentina's chairman until 2009, helping turn the club around after its previous owner drove it into bankruptcy."
